==Charts==
"Never Let Me Go" debuted at number thirty on the [[Croatian Airplay Radio Chart]] on 28 March 2012.<ref name="croatian" /> It also debuted at number nineteen on the [[ARIA Charts|Australian Singles Chart]] for the week ending 1 April 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.australian-charts.com/weekchart.asp?year=2012&date=20120408&cat=s|title=Single Top 50 - Australian-charts.com|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]. Hung Medien|date=8 April 2012|accessdate=1 April 2012}}</ref> For the week ending 29 April 2012, the song moved to a new peak at number three on the Australian Singles Chart, giving them their highest charting single to date in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.australian-charts.com/weekchart.asp?cat=s&year=2012&date=20120429|title=Single Top 50 - Australian-charts.com|publisher=Australian Recording Industry Association. Hung Medien|date=29 April 2012|accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> On the [[Ultratip|Belgian Flanders Ultratip Singles Chart]], the song debuted at number eighty three on 4 April 2012.<ref name="ultratip" /> For the week ending 7 April 2012, "Never Let Me Go" debuted at number eighty two on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref name="ukdebut">{{cite web|url=http://www.webcitation.org/query?id=1333994204222506&date=%400&fromform=1|title=Official UK Singles Top 100 - 14th April 2012|publisher=[[UK Singles Chart]]. It also went number one on the Australian Itunes Chart. [[Official Charts Company]]|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/query?id=1333994204222506&date=%400&fromform=1|archivedate=11 April 2012}}</ref>
